==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whitethroat
<hw>White"throat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of Old World warblers, esp. the common
European species (<spn>Sylvia cinerea</spn>), called also
<altname>strawsmear</altname>, <altname>nettlebird</altname>,
<altname>muff</altname>, and <altname>whitecap</altname>, the
<stype>garden whitethroat</stype>, or <stype>golden warbler</stype>
(<spn>Sylvia hortensis</spn>), and the <stype>lesser whitethroat</stype>
(<spn>Sylvia curruca</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>White-tie</ent>⟦br⟧
